############################################################
# Some examples modified from
# C++ and Object Oriented Numeric Computing
# for Scientists and Engineers.
#               Daoqi Yang  August 17, 2001 
############################################################

The makefile is different from the others. You need to set the CXX
variable to your compiler. The code is C++98 compliant, no need of
std=c++11.

compare.cpp Use of templates as policies

exprTemplate.cpp an example of expression templates

mean.cpp a simple example on function template

sort.cpp Another example of templates to specify policy. A suggestion:
for real applications use std::sort (which may accept policies) and
not the algorithm of this file

templateMeta Another example of metaprogramming

efficiency.cpp Compares functors and function pointer efficiency